The power detrating of a IRF540N transistor due to temperature is approximately 0.1% per °C. 
To calculate the power detrating at T_C=100°C, we use the formula:

Power detrating % = (Vceo - Vceo_min) / Vceo_min * 100

where Vceo is the maximum output voltage (Vceo_min) at the rated temperature

According to the data sheet, the Vceo_min at room temperature (25°C) is 3.0V, and at the maximum rating (T_C=150°C) it is 4.4V. 

Using the formula:

Power detrating % = (4.4 - 3.0) / 3.0 * 100 = 133.3%

Rounding to one significant figure, the power detrating at T_C=100°C is approximately 133%.
